===Etymology===
[[trans-]] + [[vestite]] (root verb [[vesti]] meaning to clothe/dress, english example in the general word [[vestment]] or specific example [[vest]])

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
#A person who sometimes wears [[clothes]] traditionally worn by and associated with the opposite [[sex]]; typically a male who cross-dresses occasionally by habit or compulsion.

====Usage notes====
'''''Transvestite''''' should not be confused with ''[[transgender]]'' or {{term|transsexual||someone who lives as the sex opposite that of his or her birth}}. Transvestites generally have less desire to permanently change their sex, but simply enjoy being able to cross-dress from time to time.  The term should also not be confused with {{term|drag queen||A male who wears women’s clothing for public performance}}

